The enemy convoy was put under intense fire from two sides. In the action, 2 Kirpi-type and 1 Ejder-type military vehicles were totally destroyed and 33 enemy soldiers were killed. Following the action, the occupying Turkish army carried away wreckages of vehicles and dead and wounded soldiers from the area with the support of the Atak-type helicopters. The number of dead and wounded soldiers could not be determined in the action where positions on the hill were struck effectively. Three soldiers were killed and five soldiers were wounded in the action. The occupying Turkish army has launched an operation in the area following the action. One soldier was killed in the action.